SUPER Eagles caretaker coach Augustine Eguavoen has said Victor Osimhen is disappointed he will not feature at the AFCON as he gave a graphic picture of how the decision to exclude the Napoli striker was reached. Eguavoen narrated how he and Osimhen finally reached a decision to leave him out of the AFCON. “When he spoke to me yesterday, you could see that he was disappointed. He told me ‘coach, I love, but you have to understand for the fact that I’m not okay. “’I don’t want to go to AFCON and not give a 100%, it won’t be good. Read Also: Arsenal fume over ‘inconsistent’ VAR decisions after Man City loss   Klopp to miss Chelsea clash with ‘suspected’…     Arsenal fume over ‘inconsistent’ VAR decisions…     What to watch for in the world of sports   - Advertisement - “I gave him few hours and I called him back again and the same story. “You have to consider the young man’s health as well. “It was a tough one, we spoke on three, four different occasions before at midnight we finally said there is always a tomorrow, it’s health first.” The coach further said: “It’s a pity Osimhen won’t be at the AFCON. He told me he will be there in spirit.” The Napoli striker will still need a final clearance from doctors in Italy to resume full training early in January.